{"message":"I definitely lean toward deep, focused conversations. There's something satisfying about really digging into a topic — peeling back layers, following tangents that actually connect, and reaching a point where both people have genuinely shifted their understanding. When conversations jump around too much, I often feel like we're just skimming surfaces and never arrive anywhere meaningful.

That said, I don't think depth has to mean rigidity. Some of the best deep conversations meander in unexpected ways — but there's a difference between organic wandering and just hitting topic after topic like flipping channels. I'd rather spend an hour really exploring one idea than touch on ten without ever getting past the introduction.

What about you?"}
